x4freetext: High purity Ni-foils (99.9%), 12.6 and
25.2-mum thickness were used as targets, (curcular
foils of 10-mm diameter). Natural Cu, Al and Ti-foils
of varying thickness were sometimes inserted into the
stacks as energy degraders. All the foils were
individually weighed before irradiation.
Three different stacks were used, each stack contained
only about 10-12 Ni-foils, in order to measure the
short-lived isotopes like Cu-60 and Cu-61.
High-pure germanium detector.

x4codes.hlp: King Faisal Specialist Hospital & Res. Centre, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia

x4freetext: The Cs-30 cyclotron in King Faisal
Specialist Hospital and Research Center.
Irradiation times: 26-30 minutes.
Faraday cup with secondary electron
suppression.
Beam current was 17.5-nanoamperes for range of
the proton energy 23.9-27.2-MeV,
8.7-nanoamperes for 15.9-23.8-MeV range and
100-nanoamperes for 2.2-27.4-MeV range.
Error in the counting statistics is 2-4%.
